Children.Description: Our YAF chapter brings together students to advocate for the ideas of limited government, individual freedom, free enterprise, traditional values and a strong national defense. We aim to provide a visible presence for the Conservative Movement at LSU.

Children.Title: Young Americans for Liberty at Louisiana State University
Children.Description: Young Americans for Liberty (YAL) is the largest, most active, and fastest-growing pro-liberty organization on America's college campuses. YAL seeks to identify, educate, train, and mobilize young people committed to winning on principle.

Children.Title: Young Democratic Socialists of America at LSU
Children.Description: We aim to promote a democratically socialist economy and society, as well as promote progressive policies on our campus. As an organization at LSU we hope to educate our fellow students on the principals on socialism and to dispel myths about it.

Children.Title: Young Life
Children.Description: Young Life is a Christian outreach organization that focuses on introducing Jesus to students through community. Instagram: @lsuyounglife Twitter: @lsuyounglife FB: Young Life College at LSU

Children.Title: Zamorano Agricultural Society
Children.Description: ZAS is established for the expressed purpose of assisting in the organization of cultural and agricultural exchange among students and alumni of Louisiana State University and A&M College and the Pan-American School of Agriculture.

Children.Title: Zeta Tau Alpha
Children.Description: ZTA was founded Oct. 15, 1898, at the Virginia State Female Normal School (now Longwood University) in Farmville, Va. We now have 218,000 initiated members, 159 active collegiate chapters and 235 alumnae chapters across the country.
